<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="435" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,836,929]" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,261,837,860]" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">Remarks.</emphasis>
According to the original description, 
<taxonomicName authority="Huang" authorityName="Huang" box="[674,1019,836,860]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pythamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chiabaotawow">
<emphasis box="[674,941,836,860]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">Pythamus chiabaotawow</emphasis>
Huang
</taxonomicName>
has the forewing claval veins medially confluent and lacks the ventral process of male pygofer. These are the diagnostic characters of 
<taxonomicName authority="Li (Zhang, Zhang &amp; Wei, 2010)" authorityName="Li (Zhang, Zhang &amp; Wei" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Riseveinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1196,1310,872,895]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="435">Riseveinus</emphasis>
Li (
<bibRefCitation author="Zhang" pageId="6" pageNumber="435" refString="Zhang, X, Zhang, Y. &amp; Wei, C. (2010) Review of the leafhopper genus Riseveinus Li (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae: Evacanthinae), with descriptions of two new species from China. Zootaxa, 2601, 61 - 68." type="journal article" year="2010">
Zhang, Zhang &amp; Wei, 
<number box="[308,366,906,929]" pageId="6" pageNumber="435" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, the new combination is proposed here.
</paragraph>
